    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Phymatopteris longisquamata are hypertension, which is alleviated by reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in blood vessels, and diabetes, where its antioxidant properties help mitigate glucose-induced oxidative damage. Furthermore, studies have shown that Phymatopteris longisquamata extracts exhibit hepatoprotective effects, preventing liver damage and fibrosis by scavenging free radicals and reducing lipid peroxidation. Additionally, the plant's anti-inflammatory properties have been found to alleviate symptoms of arthritis, reducing joint pain and inflammation by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities also contribute to the prevention of cardiovascular disease by reducing the risk of atherosclerosis and cardiac hypertrophy. Moreover, Phymatopteris longisquamata has been found to exhibit antimicrobial properties, inhibiting the growth of various pathogens and preventing infections such as urinary tract infections and skin infections.",
