    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Phymatopteris longisquamata are flavonoids, triterpenoids, and phenolic acids. Flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol have been identified in Phymatopteris longisquamata and have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Triterpenoids including ursolic acid and oleanolic acid have been found in the plant and have been reported to exhibit anti-inflammatory, antibacterial, and antifungal activities. Phenolic acids like ferulic acid and sinapic acid have also been identified in Phymatopteris longisquamata and have been shown to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. These constituents are responsible for the plant's medicinal properties and are likely to be responsible for its traditional uses in treating various health conditions.",
